# Patch Tuesday - May 2025 (Microsoft)

## Overview

On Tuesday, May 14, 2025, Microsoft released security updates addressing a total of 83 vulnerabilities, including 5 zero-days actively exploited and 2 publicly disclosed zero-days. Several critical flaws affect components such as Azure DevOps, Power Apps, Visual Studio, and the Windows operating system.

---

## Vulnerability Summary

| Vulnerability Type                | Count |
|----------------------------------|--------|
| Privilege Escalation             | 20     |
| Remote Code Execution            | 28     |
| Information Disclosure           | 16     |
| Denial of Service                | 7      |
| Spoofing                         | 3      |
| Security Feature Bypass          | 2      |

- Actively exploited zero-days: 5  
- Publicly disclosed zero-days: 2  
- Critical vulnerabilities: 11

---

## Actively Exploited Zero-days

| CVE             | Component                  | Impact                    |
|-----------------|----------------------------|----------------------------|
| CVE-2025-30400  | dwmcore.dll (DWM Core)     | Privilege Escalation       |
| CVE-2025-32701  | clfs.sys (CLFS)            | Privilege Escalation       |
| CVE-2025-32706  | clfs.sys (CLFS)            | Privilege Escalation       |
| CVE-2025-32709  | afd.sys (WinSock)          | Privilege Escalation       |
| CVE-2025-30397  | Microsoft Scripting Engine | Remote Code Execution      |

---

## Publicly Disclosed Zero-days

| CVE             | Component                  | Impact                    |
|-----------------|----------------------------|----------------------------|
| CVE-2025-26685  | Defender for Identity      | Spoofing                   |
| CVE-2025-32702  | Visual Studio              | Remote Code Execution      |

---

## Critical Cloud Vulnerabilities

| CVE             | Affected Service           | Vulnerability Type              | CVSS |
|-----------------|----------------------------|----------------------------------|------|
| CVE-2025-29813  | Azure DevOps               | Privilege escalation via token  | 10.0 |
| CVE-2025-29827  | Azure Automation           | Privilege Escalation            | 9.x  |
| CVE-2025-29972  | Azure Storage RP           | Server-Side Request Forgery     | 9.x  |
| CVE-2025-47733  | Microsoft Power Apps       | Server-Side Request Forgery     | 9.x  |

